.TH "fm10k_update_uc_addr_pf" 9 "fm10k_update_uc_addr_pf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fm10k_update_uc_addr_pf \- Update device unicast addresses
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "s32" fm10k_update_uc_addr_pf
.BI "(struct fm10k_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u16 glort "  ","
.BI "const u8 *mac "  ","
.BI "u16 vid "  ","
.BI "bool add "  ","
.BI "u8 flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to the HW structure
.IP "glort" 12
base resource tag for this request
.IP "mac" 12
MAC address to add/remove from table
.IP "vid" 12
VLAN ID to add/remove from table
.IP "add" 12
Indicates if this is an add or remove operation
.IP "flags" 12
flags field to indicate add and secure

This function is used to add or remove unicast addresses for
the PF.
